    <title type="html"><![CDATA[How to Adding Localized Strings in Swift?]]></title>
    <link href="http://geek-is-stupid.github.io/blog/2015/10/23/how-to-adding-localized-strings-in-swift/"/>
    <updated>2015-10-23T14:45:31+07:00</updated>
    <id>http://geek-is-stupid.github.io/blog/2015/10/23/how-to-adding-localized-strings-in-swift</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This heard like easy?</p>

<ul>
<li>Yes, but language very complex, with each language we have different way to order of word in a sentence</li>
<li>So if I have a name of user: <strong><code>"Andrew McKay"</code></strong>, and he has <strong><code>"commented"</code></strong> in a page:
The text on app will be:</li>
</ul>


<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='swift'><span class='line'><span class="s">&quot;Andrew McKay also commented&quot;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>The simple way:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='swift'><span class='line'><span class="k">let</span> <span class="n">text</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;\(user.name) &quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">NSLocalizedString</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot;also commented&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nl">comment</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p><strong>The right way (I think):</strong></p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='swift'><span class='line'><span class="k">let</span> <span class="n">text</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">NSString</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">localizedStringWithFormat</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">NSLocalizedString</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot;%@ also commented&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nl">comment</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="kt">as</span> <span class="bp">NSString</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">user</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">name</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="kt">as</span> <span class="n">String</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

]]></content>
